<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="376" pageId="10" pageNumber="375" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[831,1437,809,2049]" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,961,809,833]" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">Description</emphasis>
: . Body length 
<quantity box="[1155,1233,809,833]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="375" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
. Flagellum bristleshaped, with 41 flagellomeres; 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1167,1177,840,854]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">st</superScript>
flagellomere 2.6x longer than wide, c. 11 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1004,1017,871,885]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">th</superScript>
flagellomere square, widest flagellomeres about square; preapical flagellomere 1.1x longer than wide. Temple moderately and roundly narrowed behind eye, dorsally 0.8x as long as eye. Distance of lateral ocellus to eye 1.3x ocellar diameter. Frons coarsely rugose-punctate, with a median blunt crest-like elevation, smooth above antennal sockets. Face densely rugose-punctate and granulate, matte. Clypeus densely punctate, ± shining, apical margin slightly concave. Gena 1.2x wider than eye, densely punctate. Malar space 1.2x longer than width of mandibular base. Mandible with two teeth, lower tooth smaller than upper one. Genal carina complete, reaching hypostomal carina away from mandibular base, both carinae low.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[831,1437,809,2049]" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">Mesosoma covered with brownish hairs. Notaulus distinctly impressed in frontal 1/5 of mesoscutum. Mesoscutum densely punctate and granulate, matte. Mesopleuron and metapleuron densely rugose-punctate; juxtacoxal carina present. Scutellum moderately elevated, 1.2x wider than long, with scattered punctures and without lateral carina. Propodeum coarsely rugose. Area superomedia slightly hexagonal, 1.1x wider than long, rugose; costula weakly developed. Area petiolaris transversely rugose, with lateral carinae. Outer dentiparal edge with short blunt tooth-like extension. Hind coxa with dense punctures, without scopa. Hind femur densely punctate, 4.0x longer than wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[831,1437,809,2049]" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">
Areolet pentagonal, frontal distance of intercubiti 2x their diameter; 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[952,969,1767,1781]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">nd</superScript>
recurrent vein distal to its middle. Nervulus slightly postfurcal (1x its width).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[831,1437,809,2049]" lastBlockId="11.[151,757,231,577]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="376" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">
Metasoma strongly oxypygous, hypopygium short. Postpetiolus strongly widened, lateral field 0.8x as wide as the median one, punctate; median field largely smooth and shining, with some fine longitudinal striae and scattered punctures. 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[966,983,1959,1973]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">nd</superScript>
tergite very wide, 1.35x wider than long. Gastrocoelus impressed, with strong ridges; thyridium almost transverse, c. 0.7x as wide as the interval. 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1374,1391,2023,2037]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="375">nd</superScript>
and 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[164,178,231,245]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">rd</superScript>
tergites very finely and densely rugose-punctate, ± matte. Following tergites granulate, slightly shining. 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[164,181,295,309]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">nd</superScript>
to 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[233,246,295,309]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">th</superScript>
sternites with median folds. Ovipositor sheath slightly extending behind metasomal apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,757,231,577]" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">
Color: Black. Flagellomeres 8-12 with yellow stripes. Scutellum, triangular posterolateral spots on 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[690,700,392,406]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">st</superScript>
and 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[164,181,423,437]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">nd</superScript>
tergites and large median spots on 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[589,602,423,437]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">th</superScript>
to 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[656,669,423,437]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">th</superScript>
tergites yellow. Coxae and trochanters black; legs including trochantelli otherwise reddish. Wings with slightly yellowish tint; pterostigma yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,757,231,577]" box="[151,294,553,577]" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="376" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,756,617,865]" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,238,617,641]" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">Remark</emphasis>
: This new species belongs to group D sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="HILPERT, H." box="[151,333,649,673]" pageId="11" pageNumber="376" pagination="1 - 389" refId="ref17096" refString="HILPERT, H. 1992: Zur Systematik der Gattung Ichneumon LINNAEUS, 1758 in der Westpalaearktis. - Entomofauna Supplement 6: 1 - 389." type="journal article" year="1992">HILPERT (1992)</bibRefCitation>
. In the key of Siberian 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Ichneumon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[639,756,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">Ichneumon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="RIEDEL, M." box="[242,389,681,705]" pageId="11" pageNumber="376" pagination="1509 - 1562" refId="ref17262" refString="RIEDEL, M. 2018: Contribution to the Siberian species of Ichneumon LINNAEUS (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae, Ichneumoninae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 50: 1509 - 1562." type="journal article" year="2018">RIEDEL, 2018</bibRefCitation>
), it runs to couplet 22: 
<taxonomicName authority="LINNAEUS" authorityName="LINNAEUS" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Ichneumon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quaesitorius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">Ichneumon quaesitorius</emphasis>
LINNAEUS
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the yellow spots on 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[201,211,744,758]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">st</superScript>
and 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[279,296,743,757]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">nd</superScript>
tergites and the completely red hind tibia and tarsus. The taxon resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="MATSUMURA, 1912" authorityName="MATSUMURA" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Ichneumon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexmaculatus">
<emphasis box="[493,756,777,801]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">Ichneumon sexmaculatus</emphasis>
MATSUMURA, 1912
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the large yellow spot on 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[164,177,839,853]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="376">th</superScript>
tergite and reddish legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
